	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sun, Jul 28th 9:41 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=128443><span id=Scholar>FrostDragon</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>47 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.38]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The Glaive is a knife bladed spear used with a cutting action and piercing action.&nbsp;&nbsp;It was not very good vs cavelry so it evolved into the Glaive-Guisarme.  This added a reverse spike to snag mounted enemies and unhorse them.  IF you broaden the blade it becomes a Voulge which is a cleaver headed spear more used to slash.   A plain Guisarme is based on the peasant's prunning hook.   the Glaive(knife), Voulge(cleaver), Fauchard(sickle),  and Guisarme(prunning hook) are this class weapon.   These were used by armies of peasants.   They were common and cheap.    Glaive is not a sword.   I prefer the Bardiche(axe) or partisan(spear with tiny double axe) as  a Pole arm myself.<br><br>     </p>&nbsp;<br>Servant to Veeshan on Povar.</td></td></tr>
